We created a tidy summary of MISO results for retained intron events generated from the Ensemble gene annotation for GRCh37 version 68.

> library(readr)
> library(dplyr)
> library(tidyr)
> library(ggplot2)
> library(cowplot)
> library(viridis)
> misofn = "miso/combined-miso.tsv"
> miso = read_tsv(misofn) %>% tidyr::separate(samplename, c("genotype", "replicate"), 
+     sep = "_")

> events2gene = read_tsv("miso/event-to-gene.tsv", col_names = FALSE)
> colnames(events2gene) = c("event_name", "symbol")

I grouped the samples by genotype and calculated the mean PSI value for each event. I kept only events where a PSI value was calculated for an event in all genotypes. Then I plotted the mean PSI value for the various genotypes against each other, similar to figure 3C in the paper that was linked.

PSI plots

> misosum = miso %>% dplyr::group_by(eventtype, event_name, genotype) %>% dplyr::summarise(mpsi = mean(miso_posterior_mean)) %>% 
+     tidyr::spread(genotype, mpsi)
> misosum = misosum[complete.cases(misosum), ]
> misosum = misosum %>% mutate(prpf8_diff = ifelse(control - prpf8 > 0.1, "lower", 
+     ifelse(control - prpf8 < -0.1, "higher", "same"))) %>% mutate(prpf38_diff = ifelse(control - 
+     prpf38 > 0.1, "lower", ifelse(control - prpf38 < -0.1, "higher", "same")))

PRPF8

> ggplot(misosum, aes(control, prpf8, color = prpf8_diff)) + facet_wrap(~eventtype) + 
+     geom_point(alpha = 0.3, size = 1) + geom_abline() + xlab(", control") + 
+     ylab(", PRPF8") + scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) + panel_border() + 
+     labs(color = "") + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = 1)))

PRPF38

> ggplot(misosum, aes(control, prpf38, color = prpf38_diff)) + facet_wrap(~eventtype) + 
+     geom_point(alpha = 0.3, size = 1) + geom_abline() + xlab(", control") + 
+     ylab(", PRPF38") + scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) + panel_border() + 
+     labs(color = "") + guides(colour = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = 1)))

Wilcoxon tests

Here is a summary of the counts of events for being higher, lower or the same in PRPF8 compared to control, where higher and lower are different by 10% PSI.

Retained intron (RI)

PRPF8

> risum = subset(misosum, eventtype == "RI")
> table(risum$prpf8_diff)

higher  lower   same 
   987    141   3078 
> wilcox.test(risum$control, risum$prpf8, alternative = "less")

    Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction

data:  risum$control and risum$prpf8
W = 7530800, p-value < 2.2e-16
alternative hypothesis: true location shift is less than 0

PRPF38

> table(risum$prpf38_diff)

higher  lower   same 
   407     78   3721 
> wilcox.test(risum$control, risum$prpf38, alternative = "less")

    Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction

data:  risum$control and risum$prpf38
W = 8279400, p-value = 1.873e-07
alternative hypothesis: true location shift is less than 0

Table download

> risum = risum %>% left_join(events2gene, by = "event_name")
> write.table(risum, file = "RI_summary.csv", row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE, 
+     quote = FALSE, sep = ",")
